{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"072a45a5-282b-4b73-a5d0-d37e5759870a","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally (download from [dot.net](https://dot.net)).\n- Run `dotnet restore` to update dependencies.\n- Check for any NuGet packages with `.NET 11`-specific versions (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and update them.\n- Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` to verify everything compiles and passes.\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) doc for any API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"12ade14f-f623-442a-9e70-7937d1f9fc52","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":334},"id":"75faecd3-4333-4416-8431-beaee6e62ab2","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:58:06.973Z","parentId":"2b7ace4a-e3a7-45e3-815a-7decd9f5064d"}
